*linux-logo-4.07 (29 Aug 2003)

  29 Aug 2003; Seemant Kulleen <seemant@gentoo.org> linux-logo-4.07-r1.ebuild,
  linux-logo-4.07.ebuild, files/gentoo.logo,
  files/linux-logo-4.07-gentoo-logo.patch:
  package renamed to linux-logo instead of linux_logo

  12 Aug 2003; Stewart <stewart@gentoo.org> linux_logo-4.07-r1.ebuild:
  Marked testing for ppc - compled on a PowerMac and all seems well. Please test
  and report.

*linux_logo-4.07-r1 (07 Jun 2003)

  07 Jun 2003; Seemant Kulleen <seemant@gentoo.org> linux_logo-4.07-r1.ebuild:
  The -r1 release adds nls support (thanks to Rach Holmes), and also a
  patch from James Rowe <Jay@jnrowe.uklinux.net> via the venerable Rach Holmes,
  which adds the issue.logo to linux_logo

*linux_logo-4.07 (08 Mar 2003)

  08 Mar 2003; Troy Dack <troy@gentoo.org> linux_logo-4.07.ebuild:
  Version bump. Closes bug #16826.

*linux_logo-4.05-r1 (02 Mar 2003)

  02 Mar 2003; Troy Dack <tad@gentoo.org> linux_logo-4.05-r1.ebuild,
  files/gentoo.logo:
  Gentoo logo now includes an ASCII version. Closes Bug #15517.

